Software Requirements:
Arduino IDE (latest stable version recommended)
Python

Required Arduino libraries:
ESP32 Board Package (via Arduino Boards Manager)
WiFi Library (ESP32 built-in)
Camera Library for ESP32-CAM
TinyGPS++ (for GPS module integration)

Hardware Requirements:
ESP32-CAM
ESP32-CAM MB Base
ESP32-CAM Connector
Power Bank (optional)
Buzzer Module
NEO-6M GPS Module
Push Button Switch

Additional Notes:
Ensure proper USB drivers are installed for the ESP32-CAM programming interface.
Use a stable 5V power supply when operating the ESP32-CAM to avoid brownout issues.
Verify correct pin connections for GPS (TX/RX), buzzer, and push button before deployment.
